A weathered craftsman's wooden workbench in Studio Ghibli style, bathed in warm golden afternoon light streaming through a dusty workshop window. On the bench lies an intricate half-finished wooden automaton with delicate gears visible, surrounded by both ancient hand tools—chisels, planes, carving knives with worn handles—and modern precision instruments scattered together. Wood shavings curl across the surface like ribbons. In the background, shelves overflow with completed mechanical marvels: tiny wooden birds, dancing figures, clockwork creatures. The scene emphasizes the contrast between freely available tools and the rare skill needed to create something magical. Soft, dreamy color palette with amber, sage green, and cream tones. Detailed textures on wood grain and metal surfaces. No human figure present, but the impression of a master's patient hands lingers in every carefully placed object.
